+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_012nur9PiU1p3HX1M9eWEFhw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01FdeGfQiESKtt2jPqrd4yvu","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-07-reactive-spreadsheet-design.md","content":"# Reactive Spreadsheet Engine — Design\n\n## Architecture\n\nSingle-package TypeScript library with four source modules:\n\n- **`src/types.ts`** — AST node types, cell value type aliases\n- **`src/utils.ts`** — Cell reference parsing, column letter ↔ number conversion, range expansion\n- **`src/parser.ts`** — Tokenizer + recursive-descent formula parser producing an AST\n- **`src/index.ts`** — `Spreadsheet` class: public API, dependency graph, reactive evaluation\n\n## Data Flow\n\n1. `set(cell, value)` is called\n2. If value is a string starting with `=`, parse it into an AST via `parser.ts`\n3. Extract dependency references from the AST\n4. Update the dependency graph (cell → set of cells it depends on, and reverse map)\n5. Cycle detection via DFS from the target cell through its transitive dependents\n6. Evaluate the cell's AST to produce a computed value\n7. Topologically sort all transitive dependents and recompute each in order\n\n## Formula Parser\n\nRecursive descent with these precedence levels (low to high):\n1. Comparison: `>`, `<`, `>=`, `<=`, `=`, `<>`\n2. Addition: `+`, `-`\n3. Multiplication: `*`, `/`\n4. Unary: `-`\n5. Primary: number literal, string literal, boolean literal, cell reference, function call, parenthesized expression\n\nRanges (`A1:A5`) are only valid as function arguments, not as standalone expressions.\n\n## Dependency Graph\n\n- `dependencies: Map<string, Set<string>>` — cell → cells it reads from\n- `dependents: Map<string, Set<string>>` — cell → cells that read from it (reverse)\n- On `set()`, old dependencies are removed before new ones are added\n- Cycle detection: DFS from the cell being set through `dependents` — if we encounter the cell itself, it's a cycle\n\n## Reactive Recalculation\n\nAfter evaluating the set cell, collect all transitive dependents via BFS/DFS, topologically sort them, and evaluate each in order. This ensures each cell is recalculated only after all its dependencies have been updated.\n\n## Error Handling\n\n- Circular references: throw an Error on `set()` (and roll back the change)\n- Division by zero: produce `Infinity` or `-Infinity` (standard JS behavior)\n- Invalid references in formulas: return `null` (empty cell)\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n- Unit tests for `utils.ts` (cell ref parsing, column conversion, range expansion)\n- Unit tests for `parser.ts` (tokenization, AST structure)\n- Integration tests for `Spreadsheet` class covering:\n  - Basic value setting/getting\n  - Formula evaluation (arithmetic, references)\n  - Built-in functions (SUM, AVERAGE, MIN, MAX, COUNT, IF)\n  - Range evaluation (column, row, block)\n  - Reactive updates (direct and transitive)\n  - Circular reference detection\n  - Edge cases (empty cells, string values, boolean values)\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":515,"cache_read_input_tokens":23946,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":515},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b246dfe4-021c-4239-9ce1-7fa9c34fdd5c","uuid":"ece8fdcb-30f4-4c87-95be-c7a37d7b44b4"}
